323
00:15:58,540 --> 00:16:03,160
which is simply the negative of its reflection

324
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:06,200
about the diagonal.

325
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:08,800
That means there are three,

326
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:11,400
and only three, independent components

327
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:14,580
of this anti-symmetric tensor.

328
00:16:14,580 --> 00:16:17,000
Well, you can always put three components,

329
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,880
and you can line them up, and

330
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:22,760
call them the components of a vector.

331
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:26,760
That doesn't mean that they transform properly as a vector.

332
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:31,180
But, these three objects do transform properly as a vector,

333
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:34,000
if we make the right identifications.

334
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,000
In particular,

335
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:41,000
those who know what a cross product is,

336
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,380
will already see the pattern that these are the

337
00:16:43,380 --> 00:16:45,760
components of the cross product of a cross product.

338
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:46,260
So, we have a cross product, and we have

339
00:16:46,260 --> 00:16:46,760
a cross product, and we have a cross product.

340
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:47,820
So, we have a cross product,

341
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:48,880
and we have a cross product.

342
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:51,880
But in particular, I'll tell you which components they are.

343
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:54,720
They are the components

344
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:57,960
A1B2, that's C3.

345
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:59,640
Let's write it over here.

346
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:01,560
No, let's do it over here.

347
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:03,640
C3.

348
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,760
This one is C3.

349
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:09,700
One, two, three.

350
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:10,740
What about this one?

351
00:17:10,740 --> 00:17:14,319
What would you put here?

352
00:17:14,319 --> 00:17:15,760
Temporarily, let's put C2 there.

353
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:16,760
Okay.

354
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:21,760
And this one, of course, would be C1.

355
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:24,260
In other words, these three objects

356
00:17:24,260 --> 00:17:26,760
can be placed in one-to-one correspondence

357
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:31,760
with the components of this anti-symmetric tensor here.

358
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:34,760
The anti-symmetric tensor is one form of the cross product,

359
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:39,760
which in fact generalizes to other dimensions.

360
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:42,760
In other dimensions, an anti-symmetric tensor

361
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:44,260
will not have the same

362
00:17:44,260 --> 00:17:45,760
number of components as a vector.

363
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:48,760
So this is special to three dimensions.

364
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:51,760
In higher dimensions, there's no such thing

365
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:55,760
as the cross product of two vectors giving another vector.

366
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:58,260
But there always is the

367
00:17:58,260 --> 00:18:00,760
cross product giving an anti-symmetric tensor.

368
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:02,760
So the generalization of the

369
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:04,760
cross product to other dimensions

370
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:06,760
is the anti-symmetric tensor.

371
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:08,760
For three dimensions, it's fine to

372
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,760
think of it as a vector.

373
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:13,760
Now, it's actually C2 here.

