411
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:02,760
Now, what's going on here?

412
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:04,760
What's the geometry of this?

413
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:07,760
An anti-symmetric tensor has two indices.

414
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:11,760
Every component of it is associated with two axes.

415
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:14,760
An x-axis and a y-axis.

416
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:15,760
Okay.

417
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:19,260
Well, the xy-axis, the xy component

418
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:22,760
of the anti-symmetric tensor is simply

419
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:26,760
identified with the z component of the vector.

420
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:29,760
It's clear that it's ambiguous.

421
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:32,760
Do you describe a vector by

422
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:35,760
describing the plane that it's perpendicular to,

423
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:38,260
in which case you're describing it

424
00:20:38,260 --> 00:20:40,760
by a pair of vectors, namely the,

425
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:42,760
the pair of vectors that defines a

426
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:44,760
plane, or do you describe it by the

427
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:47,760
arrow that's sticking out of the plane?

428
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:50,260
The two ways of describing the vector,

429
00:20:50,260 --> 00:20:52,760
one, by just an arrow sticking out,

430
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:55,760
is describing it by its vector components.

431
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,760
The other way of describing it is

432
00:20:57,760 --> 00:20:59,760
in terms of the planes that are

433
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:01,760
perpendicular to those vector components,

434
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,760
and that's the description in

435
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:05,760
terms of the anti-symmetric tensor.

436
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,760
Now, the difficult thing, it's not

437
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:09,760
very difficult, it's rather easy, but

